elfarol

Interface Agent

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AgentAverage, AgentMarkov, AgentRan, AgentWeighted

    public interface Agent
    An interface representing an agent in the El Farol Bar model. Defines a common set of public methods for agents in the simulation. This interface was extracted from the Agent class written by Richard O. Legendi.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean isAttending()
      Returns the value of attend.
      void updateAttendance()
      Makes the agent update its attendance level based on its attendance prediction.
      void updatePredictions()
      Scheduled update method for the agent's predictions.

    • Method Detail

      • isAttending

        boolean isAttending()
        Returns the value of attend.
        Returns:
        true if the agent attends the bar in the current time step (if called after the updateAttendance() function); false otherwise

      • updatePredictions

        void updatePredictions()
        Scheduled update method for the agent's predictions. This is called by the model every tick prior to updateAttendance() and can be used to update the agent's beliefs prior to making predictions. Agents which do not require scheduled beliefs updating do nothing when this method is called.

      • updateAttendance

        void updateAttendance()
        Makes the agent update its attendance level based on its attendance prediction. This is called by the model after updatePredictions() and prior to isAttending()
